<h1>Help</h1>

<p>
	<b>What is a findpost?</b><br>

	Findposts are used to describe the person you're looking for.  A findpost is a searchable by "Skales" which is another word for the "search criteria".  Use "Find You" to SEARCH Findposts.  Use "Find Me" to CREATE findposts.<br>
</p>

<p>
	<b>Suggested "Skales":</b><br>
	1. Purpose<br>
	2. Location<br>
	3. Time<br>
	4. Goal<br>
	5. Interests<br>
	6. Condition<br>
	8. Qualification<br>
	9. Personality<br>
	10. Additional Information<br>
</p>

<p>
	<b>Getting started with Skalefree requires a few simple steps:</b><br><br>

	1. Signup or login to skalefree.net. Choose a name that is not your real name. Skalefree is used anonymously to protect your privacy. <br><br>
	2. Click the "Find Me" link to create a findpost with "Skales" describing the person you're looking for.<br><br>
	3. Click the "Find You" link to search through the "Skales" of existing findposts.<br><br>
	4. Check a findpost owner's profile and node status (reputation) to evaluate connection potential.<br><br>
	5. Start a conversation with findpost owner. Messages will also be delivered to your email. Check your spambox if you don't see them.<br><br>
	6. Strike a deal.<br><br>
	7. Improve that user's node status if you are satisfied, otherwise lower it.<br><br>
	8. Delete your findpost once you're done with it.<br>
</p>

